e: Agro</span><hr size=1> Best advise I could give anyone is:<br>
Don't ever choose one pet as your exclussive solo pet.<br>
<br>
All pets have advantages, and depending on what is needed, choose what is best.<br>
<br>
For me, it's about downtime and speed of the kill can change downtime.<br>
<br>
Fire (pre 50): use when ever you can get away with it.  It's damage shield will kill faster, there for making smaller downtimes.<br>
<br>
Water: Most damaging in melee, regens real fast but can't handle mobs that ignore the pet.<br>
<br>
Air: Good against casters and high ac/agi, it's stun also reduces the amount of damage it takes.  This reduces downtime.  Against mobs that seem to chase you some, but not real bad, the stun can be used in place of root.<br>
<br>
Earth: When you need a mob rooted, because he's going to come chase you down, earth is great.  It also allows you to chain blast more than anyother pet.  It's good against the big bad mobs that heavy tanking and fast blasting is needed, since mobs can't chase you while rooted, which allows you to chain blast.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzantenvaliturus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zanten Valiturus</A> at: 11/20/00 1:16:36 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uezno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ezno</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/posticons/eyes.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 242<br> <font color=#333333>(11/20/00 8:33:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=105.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Agro</span><hr size=1> <br>
I like to use Earth against tough High HP High Dmg MoBs (like Ice Giants) because their root combined with Char means very fast damage output (i.e. I take them down quickly).      <br>
<br>
But, overall, I try to use (pre-50) Fire as much as possible when soloing.   They take the least amount of time and mana to solo with plus you can easily outdamage the pet (always important to consider in soloing). <br>
<br>
Air is nice.  I find their stuns to be good taunts, they take the least damage and thus healing them is the most mana efficient.   (Just got 53rd Air that I will play with to compare to 51 earth and 49 fire for soloing). <br>
<br>
Water I haven't used since 34th so I can't talk about too much.  Too much a pain to research ;)  Looking forward to 54th Water for those trips to Skyfire with a Druid/Enchanter or Necromancer.  <br>
<br>
Mainly, I've found Fire/Earth as my two favorite solo pets.  Air I like when grouping to decrease dmg on tanks.  Water will become my fear-kiting pet and prob pet of choice when a Shaman is present.  <p> <br>
